<emphasis box="[363,614,265,290]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">Chondria collinsiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is restricted to the Caribbean Sea, the South Atlantic, and the Indian Ocean (
<bibRefCitation author="Jaasund, E." box="[243,410,303,329]" pageId="4" pageNumber="57" refId="ref7427" refString="Jaasund, E. (1976) Intertidal seaweeds in Tanzania. University of Tromso, Tromso, 159 pp." type="book" year="1976">Jaasund 1976</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Littler, D. S. &amp; Littler, M. M." box="[423,637,303,329]" pageId="4" pageNumber="57" pagination="1 - 41" refId="ref7723" refString="Littler, D. S., Littler, M. M. &amp; Brooks. B. L. (1995) Marine algae and seagrasses from the Tobacco Range Fracture Zone, Belize, C. A. Atoll Research Bulletin 429: 1 - 41." type="journal article" year="1995">
